  <main class="content">
<p>Our policies exist to safeguard the values that define Moi High School Kabarak: <strong>commitment, fairness, and integrity</strong>. They establish a clear, consistent framework within which every student can flourish  academically, socially, and spiritually  and every member of staff can do their best work.</p>
<p>Each policy listed below reflects our pursuit of excellence within a Christian, learner-centered environment. Policies are reviewed regularly by the school management and Board to ensure they remain current and aligned with the school's mission.</p>

<h2 class="section-heading">Policy Framework</h2>
<div class="policy-grid"><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Academic Policy</h3><p>Standards for teaching, learning, assessment, and academic integrity across the school.</p><div class="policy-meta">Education</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Code of Conduct</h3><p>Expected behaviour for all students, both on and off campus, in line with our Christian ethos.</p><div class="policy-meta">Discipline</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Boarding &amp; Welfare</h3><p>Rules and procedures governing dormitory life, student welfare, and house leadership.</p><div class="policy-meta">Boarding</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>School Uniform Policy</h3><p>Approved attire for all students, including sports kit and Sunday-best dress code.</p><div class="policy-meta">Uniform</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>ICT &amp; Mobile Devices</h3><p>Acceptable use of technology, internet access, and personal electronics.</p><div class="policy-meta">Technology</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Safeguarding &amp; Child Protection</h3><p>Comprehensive safeguarding framework to protect every student's wellbeing.</p><div class="policy-meta">Safety</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Health &amp; Medical Policy</h3><p>Sanatorium procedures, medication handling, and emergency response protocols.</p><div class="policy-meta">Health</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Library &amp; Resources</h3><p>Borrowing rules, study expectations, and care of school learning materials.</p><div class="policy-meta">Library</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Chapel &amp; Religious Life</h3><p>Worship attendance, religious instruction, and fostering Christian values.</p><div class="policy-meta">Faith</div></div><div class="policy-card"><div class="policy-icon"></div><h3>Anti-Bullying Policy</h3><p>Zero-tolerance framework for bullying, harassment, and discrimination of any kind.</p><div class="policy-meta">Wellbeing</div></div></div>

<div class="principles-banner">
  <h3>Guiding Principles</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Every policy is anchored in our Christian foundation and mission</li>
    <li>Fairness and consistency apply equally to every student and staff member</li>
    <li>Parents and guardians are partners in upholding the school's standards</li>
    <li>Policies are reviewed regularly by the Board of Governors</li>
    <li>Detailed policy documents are available from the school administration office on request</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<p style="margin-top:2rem"><em>For detailed policy documents, please contact the school administration office or refer to the Student/Parent Handbook issued at admission.</em></p>
